### API Reference and Request Body Formats
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension
# Replace {{token}} with your actual Bearer token after logging in

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### 1. Unified Login (Admin / MFA)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/admin-login/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Create School
POST {{baseUrl}}/create/schools/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "school_name": "School of Engineering",
    "school_code": "SOE"
}

### 3. List Schools
GET {{baseUrl}}/create/schools/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Create Department Admin Assignment
# Cascading Selection Requirement: Select School -> Degree -> Department -> Faculty
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/dept-admin/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "faculty_id": "uuid-of-faculty",
    "school_id": "uuid-of-school",
    "degree_id": "uuid-of-degree",
    "department_id": "uuid-of-department",
    "is_active": true
}

### 5. Bulk Student Upload (Excel)
# This usually requires multipart/form-data
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/students/upload-excel/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="students.xlsx"
Content-Type: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet

< ./path/to/your/students.xlsx
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 6. Create Course
POST {{baseUrl}}/course-configuration/courses/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "course_name": "Digital Logic Design",
    "course_code": "CS101",
    "course_type": "CORE",
    "course_category": "THEORY",
    "batch": "2024-2028",
    "credit_value": 3,
    "lecture_hours": 3,
    "tutorial_hours": 0,
    "practical_hours": 0,
    "school": "uuid-of-school",
    "degree": "uuid-of-degree",
    "department": "uuid-of-department",
    "regulation": "uuid-of-regulation"
}

### 7. Create Academic Calendar
POST {{baseUrl}}/academic/calendars/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Academic Calendar 2024-25",
    "school": "uuid-of-school",
    "degree": "uuid-of-degree",
    "department": "uuid-of-department",
    "regulation": "uuid-of-regulation",
    "batch": "2024-2028",
    "semester": "uuid-of-semester"
}

### 8. Token Refresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/token/refresh/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refresh": "your-refresh-token"
}

### 9. List Configured Courses (Filtered by Dept/Regulation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/course-configuration/courses/?department=uuid-of-dept&regulation=uuid-of-reg
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Roles Dashboard Summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/roles/summary/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
